--- !u!114 &4512410604008640795
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 2711081185484452047}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 73db8026ffc4171418e993292aecaca7, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  Names:
  - Gobbo The Boss
  CorrectLines:
  - Finally, lazybones.
  - I thought you'd never make it to my office, having fallen head over heels into
    the Archives again, haha!
  - Anyway... YOU... You're doing a surprisingly good job! But... Only by the standards
    of this dump!
  - I'm disbanding DOPMA. Not only is it not bringing me any truffies, even though
    those idiots promised me at least a thousand a month!
  - "Ahem... And many unscrupulous mages have been bribing lawyers to talk nonsense
    so they could get our truffies\u2014or rather, perks\u2014right in their robes.
    Or they were simply getting rid of unwanted artifacts!"
  - Here you go.
  - '*Gobbo The Boss gave you one truffie... Generously*'
  - You deserve it for your work. But now you're fired. Get out.
  - The ending "BUREAUCRACY LOST TO TRUFFIES" has been achieved!
  WrongLines:
  - Finally, lazybones.
  - I thought you'd never make it to my office, having fallen head over heels into
    the Archives again, haha!
  - Anyway... YOU... You're doing a terrible job!
  - To think you could screw up SO badly at THIS job!
  - You can't even THINK about truffies, let alone Magical Artifacts!
  - Fired! Get out!
  - The ending "BUREAUCRACY WINS... you?" has been achieved!
  NeutralLines:
  - Finally, lazybones.
  - I thought you'd never make it to my office, having fallen head over heels into
    the Archives again, haha!
  - Anyway... YOU... Your results are almost average! Not bad for a couch potato
    like you!
  - But alas, I'm disbanding DOPMA... Not only is it not bringing me any truffies,
    even though those idiots promised me at least a thousand a month!
  - "Ahem... And many unscrupulous mages have been bribing lawyers to talk nonsense
    so they could get our truffies\u2014or rather, perks\u2014right in their robes.
    Or they were simply getting rid of unwanted artifacts!"
  - And now you're fired. Get out.
  - The ending "Oh nO! BUREAUCRACY WINS TRUFFIES!" has been achieved!
--- !u!82 &4512410604008640796
AudioSource:
